## Project conventions — read first

Before answering or editing code, read the files in
`{{ ai_folder }}/instructions/`. They are authoritative — if anything
in this file conflicts, they win.

General (always):
- general/coding-conventions.md — language-agnostic style and idioms
- general/architecture.md       — DDD layering rules
- general/ddd.md                — domain modelling
- general/tdd.md                — test-driven micro-implementation
- general/testing.md            — what / where / how to test
- general/security.md           — security posture
{% if 'python' in languages %}
Python (when touching Python):
- python/zen.md          — PEP 20
- python/style.md        — formatting, type hints, docstrings
- python/tooling.md      — uv, ruff, mypy, pytest
- python/design.md       — composition, DI, protocols
- python/patterns.md     — value objects, policy, context object, UoW
- python/code-smells.md  — refactor against this taxonomy
- python/testing.md      — pytest, hypothesis, mutation, classical school
{% endif %}{% if 'rust' in languages %}
Rust (when touching Rust):
- rust/style.md          — naming, edition, error handling, lints
- rust/tooling.md        — cargo, clippy, rustfmt
- rust/design.md         — ownership, traits, type-state
- rust/patterns.md       — newtype, builder, RAII, variant dispatch
- rust/code-smells.md    — refactor against this taxonomy
- rust/testing.md        — #[cfg(test)], proptest, criterion
{% endif %}{% if 'typescript' in languages %}
